{"title_page": "Lootmaar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{notability|film|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lootmaar\n| image          = Lootmaarfilm.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = Dev Anand\n| producer       = Dev Anand\n| writer         =\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Dev Anand]]<br />[[Tina Munim]]<br />[[Rakhee Gulzar]]<br />[[Nirupa Roy]]\n| music          = [[Rajesh Roshan]]\n| cinematography =\n| editing        =\n| distributor    =\n| released       = {{Film date|1980}}\n| runtime        =\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         =\n}}\n\n'''''Lootmaar''''' ({{trans|Depredator}}) is a [[1980]] Hindi [[mystery film]]<ref>https://bollybusiness.wordpress.com/2012/04/24/lootmaar-1980-review-from-filmfare-1980/</ref> produced and directed by [[Dev Anand]]. The film stars [[Dev Anand]], [[Tina Munim]], [[Mehmood]], [[Nirupa Roy]], [[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[Kader Khan]], [[Ranjeet]], [[Shakti Kapoor]], [[Simple Kapadia]], [[Shreeram Lagoo]] and [[Rakhee Gulzar]]. The film's music is by [[Rajesh Roshan]].\n\n==Plot==\nIndian Air Force pilot [[Bhagat]] lives with his wife, [[Rakshasa|Raksha]] and a young son. While going to the bank one day, the family find that the bank is being held up. The bank-robbers panic at the arrival of the police, and fire randomly, killing Raksha instantly. Bhagat witnesses this horrific spectacle and is unable to do anything to save his wife. The robbers were masked, but one of them had a tear in his shoe and another was wearing a locket, very similar to the one worn by his wife. Bhagat's inquiries take him to the northernmost hilly regions of [[India]], where he must confront the past, as well as seek out the elusive killers and bring them to justice, not knowing that in so doing he will be endangering the life of his son.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Dev Anand]] as Wing Commander Bhagat / Jim Darcy\n* [[Tina Munim]] as Neela Ramniklal\n* [[Mehmood Ali]] as John Gonzalves\n* [[Nirupa Roy]] as Satyavati\n* [[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]] as Vikram\n* [[Prem Chopra]] as Damodar\n* [[Kader Khan]]  \t\t\n* [[Ranjeet]] as Peter\n* [[Shakti Kapoor]]\t\t\n* [[Simple Kapadia]] as\tRani\n* [[Shreeram Lagoo]] as\tSeth Ramniklal\n* [[Om Shivpuri]] as Mr. Bhagat\n* [[Sudhir Dalvi]] as Pandit\n* [[Ram Mohan]]\tas Police Inspector\n* [[Sharat Saxena]] as Police Inspector\n* [[Narendra Nath]]\t\t\n* [[Raakhee Gulzar]] as Raksha Bhagat\n* [[Birbal]]\n* [[Kalpana Iyer]] as Dancer\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe film's soundtrack was composed by [[Rajesh Roshan]] and the lyrics were penned by [[Amit Khanna]].\n\n# \"Main Aur Tu Kar Le Dosti\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n# \"Paas Ho Tum Magar Karib Nahi\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n# \"Piya Hum Saat Mulk Ka Pani\" - [[Kishore Kumar]]\n# \"Aaj Ka Din\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Kishore kumar]]\n# \"Piya Hum\" - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Mehmood]]\n# \"Jab Chaye Mera Jadoo\" - [[Asha Bhosle]]\n# \"Hans Tu Hardam Khushiya Ya Gum\" - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Varsha Bhosle]], [[Shivangi Kolhapure]]\n# \"Hans Tu Hardam\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n<ref>http://hindigeetmala.net/movie/lootmaar.htm</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0154788|Lootmaar}}\n\n[[Category:1980 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1980s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dev Anand]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Rajesh Roshan]]\n[[Category:Indian mystery films]]\n\n{{1980s-Hindi-film-stub}}\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{notability|film|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lootmaar\n| image          = Lootmaarfilm.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = Dev Anand\n| producer       = Dev Anand\n| writer         =\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Dev Anand]]<br />[[Tina Munim]]<br />[[Rakhee Gulzar]]<br />[[Nirupa Roy]]\n| music          = [[Rajesh Roshan]]\n| cinematography =\n| editing        =\n| distributor    =\n| released       = {{Film date|1980}}\n| runtime        =\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         =\n}}\n\n'''''Lootmaar''''' ({{trans|Depredator}}) is a [[1980]] Hindi [[mystery film]]<ref>https://bollybusiness.wordpress.com/2012/04/24/lootmaar-1980-review-from-filmfare-1980/</ref> produced and directed by [[Dev Anand]]. The film stars [[Dev Anand]], [[Tina Munim]], [[Mehmood]], [[Nirupa Roy]], [[Amjad Khan]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[Kader Khan]], [[Ranjeet]], [[Shakti Kapoor]], [[Simple Kapadia]], [[Shreeram Lagoo]] and [[Rakhee Gulzar]]. The film's music is by [[Rajesh Roshan]].\n\n==Plot==\nIndian Air Force pilot [[Bhagat]] lives with his wife, [[Rakshasa|Raksha]] and a young son. While going to the bank one day, the family find that the bank is being held up. The bank-robbers panic at the arrival of the police, and fire randomly, killing Raksha instantly. Bhagat witnesses this horrific spectacle and is unable to do anything to save his wife. The robbers were masked, but one of them had a tear in his shoe and another was wearing a locket, very similar to the one worn by his wife. Bhagat's inquiries take him to the northernmost hilly regions of [[India]], where he must confront the past, as well as seek out the elusive killers and bring them to justice, not knowing that in so doing he will be endangering the life of his son.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Dev Anand]] as Wing Commander Bhagat / Jim Darcy\n* [[Tina Munim]] as Neela Ramniklal\n* [[Mehmood Ali]] as John Gonzalves\n* [[Nirupa Roy]] as Satyavati\n* [[Amjad Khan]] as Vikram\n* [[Prem Chopra]] as Damodar\n* [[Kader Khan]]  \t\t\n* [[Ranjeet]] as Peter\n* [[Shakti Kapoor]]\t\t\n* [[Simple Kapadia]] as\tRani\n* [[Shreeram Lagoo]] as\tSeth Ramniklal\n* [[Om Shivpuri]] as Mr. Bhagat\n* [[Sudhir Dalvi]] as Pandit\n* [[Ram Mohan]]\tas Police Inspector\n* [[Sharat Saxena]] as Police Inspector\n* [[Narendra Nath]]\t\t\n* [[Raakhee Gulzar]] as Raksha Bhagat\n* [[Birbal]]\n* [[Kalpana Iyer]] as Dancer\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe film's soundtrack was composed by [[Rajesh Roshan]] and the lyrics were penned by [[Amit Khanna]].\n\n# \"Main Aur Tu Kar Le Dosti\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n# \"Paas Ho Tum Magar Karib Nahi\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n# \"Piya Hum Saat Mulk Ka Pani\" - [[Kishore Kumar]]\n# \"Aaj Ka Din\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Kishore kumar]]\n# \"Piya Hum\" - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Mehmood]]\n# \"Jab Chaye Mera Jadoo\" - [[Asha Bhosle]]\n# \"Hans Tu Hardam Khushiya Ya Gum\" - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Varsha Bhosle]], [[Shivangi Kolhapure]]\n# \"Hans Tu Hardam\" - [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n<ref>http://hindigeetmala.net/movie/lootmaar.htm</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0154788|Lootmaar}}\n\n[[Category:1980 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1980s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dev Anand]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Rajesh Roshan]]\n[[Category:Indian mystery films]]\n\n{{1980s-Hindi-film-stub}}\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toAmjad Khan(link changed toAmjad Khan (actor); link changed toAmjad Khan (actor)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lootmaar"}
{"title_page": "Divyadarshan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = \n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|10|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kollam]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| years_active       = 2012 &ndash; present\n| parents            = E. A. Rajendran<br/>Sandhya Rajendran\n| relatives          = [[Mukesh (actor)|Mukesh]] (uncle)\n| occupation         = Actor\n}}\n\n'''Divyadarshan''' (born 26 October 1986) is an [[actor]] from [[Kerala]], [[India]]. Divyadarshan made his debut in [[Malayalam]] through the movie ''[[Hide n' Seek]]'' in 2012 and has acted in seven movies since then.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/A-surprise-debut-for-Divyadarshan/articleshow/15388143.cms| title=A surprise debut for Divyadarshan}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDivyadarshan was born in Pattathanam [[Kollam]], [[Kerala]] as the only son of actor E. A. Rajendran and Sandhya Rajendran. He is the grandson of theater artist and writer O. Madhavan and Vijayakumari, who is also an actress. He is also the nephew of actor [[Mukesh (actor)|Mukesh]].Divyadarshan is married to Ashwathi Raj and has a daughter .\n\n==Career==\nThe actor made his entry into the [[Malayalam cinema]] industry in a lead role through Anil's ''[[Hide n' Seek]]'', which was also his home production. He also acted in the movies ''Mr. Bean'', ''Teens'' and ''Kootathil Oral''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cochintalkies.com/celebrity/divya-darshan-filmography.html| title=Divyadarshan Filimography}}</ref>\nIn 2014, Divyadarshan played the lead in Jahangir Shams's ''[[Karanavar]]''.\n\nThe actor will be seen in [[Anil Radhakrishnan Menon]]'s upcoming movie ''[[Lord Livingstone 7000 Kandi]]'', a comical fantasy film.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Year\n\n! Director\n|-\n|''[[Hide n' Seek]]''||2012|||Anil\n|-\n|''[[Teens]]''||2013||Jahangir Shams\n|-\n|''Mr Bean''||2013||Reji Paul\n|-\n|''Kootathil oral''||2014||K.Padmakumar\n|-\n|''[[Karanavar]]''|||2014||Jahangir Shams\n|-\n|''[[Lord Livingstone 7000 Kandi]]''||2015||[[Anil Radhakrishnan Menon]]\n|- \n|''[[Masterpiece (2017 film)|Masterpiece]]''||2017||[[Ajai Vasudev]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Divyadarshan}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Kollam]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = \n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|10|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kollam]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| years_active       = 2012 &ndash; present\n| parents            = E. A. Rajendran<br/>Sandhya Rajendran\n| relatives          = [[Mukesh (actor)|Mukesh]] (uncle)\n| occupation         = Actor\n}}\n\n'''Divyadarshan''' (born 26 October 1986) is an [[actor]] from [[Kerala]], [[India]]. Divyadarshan made his debut in [[Malayalam]] through the movie ''[[Hide n' Seek]]'' in 2012 and has acted in seven movies since then.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/A-surprise-debut-for-Divyadarshan/articleshow/15388143.cms| title=A surprise debut for Divyadarshan}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDivyadarshan was born in Pattathanam [[Kollam]], [[Kerala]] as the only son of actor E. A. Rajendran and Sandhya Rajendran. He is the grandson of theater artist and writer O. Madhavan and Vijayakumari, who is also an actress. He is also the nephew of actor [[Mukesh (actor)|Mukesh]].\n\n==Career==\nThe actor made his entry into the [[Malayalam cinema]] industry in a lead role through Anil's ''[[Hide n' Seek]]'', which was also his home production. He also acted in the movies ''Mr. Bean'', ''Teens'' and ''Kootathil Oral''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cochintalkies.com/celebrity/divya-darshan-filmography.html| title=Divyadarshan Filimography}}</ref>\nIn 2014, Divyadarshan played the lead in Jahangir Shams's ''[[Karanavar]]''.\n\nThe actor will be seen in [[Anil Radhakrishnan Menon]]'s upcoming movie ''[[Lord Livingstone 7000 Kandi]]'', a comical fantasy film.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Year\n\n! Director\n|-\n|''[[Hide n' Seek]]''||2012|||Anil\n|-\n|''[[Teens]]''||2013||Jahangir Shams\n|-\n|''Mr Bean''||2013||Reji Paul\n|-\n|''Kootathil oral''||2014||K.Padmakumar\n|-\n|''[[Karanavar]]''|||2014||Jahangir Shams\n|-\n|''[[Lord Livingstone 7000 Kandi]]''||2015||[[Anil Radhakrishnan Menon]]\n|- \n|''[[Masterpiece (2017 film)|Masterpiece]]''||2017||[[Ajai Vasudev]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Divyadarshan}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Kollam]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "name_user": "2001:16a2:3a8f:e200:d13c:377b:da09:d2e1", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divyadarshan"}
{"title_page": "Des Pardes (1978 film)", "text_new": "{{About||the 1983 film|Des Pardes (1983 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Des Pardes\n| image =Des Pardes (1978).jpg\n| caption =Poster\n| director = [[Dev Anand]]\n| producer = [[Dev Anand]]<br />Amit Khanna<br />Navketan<br />Navketan International Films\n| writer = [[Dev Anand]]<br />Suraj Sanim\n| narrator =\n| starring = [[Dev Anand]]<br />[[Tina Munim]]<br />[[Mehmood]]<br />[[Pran (actor)|Pran]]<br />[[Ajit Khan]]<br />[[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]]<br />[[Prem Chopra]]\n| music = [[Rajesh Roshan]]<br />[[Amit Khanna]] (lyrics)\n| cinematography = Fali Mistry<br />D. K. Prabhakar\n| editing =\n| distributor =\n| released = {{Film date|1978|6|29|df=y}}\n| runtime =\n| country = [[India]]\n| language = Hindi\n| budget =\n}}\n'''''Des Pardes''''' ({{lit|Home and Abroad}}) is a [[Bollywood films of 1978|1978]] Hindi film, produced and directed by [[Dev Anand]]. This family drama stars [[Dev Anand]] and [[Tina Munim]] (in her debut film), with [[Ajit Khan]], [[Pran (actor)|Pran]], [[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]], [[Shreeram Lagoo]], [[Tom Alter]], [[Bindu]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[A. K. Hangal]], [[Sujit Kumar]], [[Mehmood]] and [[Paintal]] in the supporting cast. For the first time, [[Dev Anand]] chose comparatively new music director [[Rajesh Roshan]] for this film, who did full justice to his selection as most of the songs became quite popular. The film received a Filmfare award for its sets and also received a nomination for best music director.\n\nThe message of this film is about the trend with some people, at the time, to earn money from foreign lands and that innocent ones being trapped and tormented by the illicit operators.\n\n== Plot ==\nSamir Sahni is a farmer living with his mom, dad, wife, Rama, a young daughter, and his younger brother, Veer. Samir gets an offer to work in the U.K., and departs accordingly. He would like to settle there, and after doing so, would like his family to also join him. The years go by, and Samir keeps in touch with his family regularly. Then the Sahni family stop receiving any letters from him, and are anxious to know what has happened to him. Veer is asked to travel to U.K. to find out, and he does so. What he finds are tens of thousands of East Indians on fake passports, working for less than minimum wages, poor unhealthy conditions, fear of being deported, and paying half of their earnings to fellow East Indians who had got them here through the underground. Veer finds no sign of his brother, and sets out to investigate, only to find deceit, murder, and that his very own life in danger.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Dev Anand]] as Veer Sahni\n*[[Pran (actor)|Pran]] as Samir Sahni\n*[[Gajanan Jagirdar]] as Mr. Sahni\n*[[Indrani Mukherjee]] as Rama Sahni\n*[[Ajit Khan]] as Gurnam\n*[[Tom Alter]] as Inspector Martin\n*[[Bindu (actress)|Bindu]] as Sylvia\n*[[Prem Chopra]] as Bansilal\n*[[A. K. Hangal]] as Pujari\n*[[Jankidas]] as Daiyal\n*[[Bharat Kapoor]] as Murarilal\n*[[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]] as Boota Singh / Avtar Singh\n*[[Sujit Kumar]] as Gangaram\n*[[Shreeram Lagoo]] as Mr. Burns\n*[[Mehmood Ali|Mehmood]] as Anwar\n*[[Tina Munim]] as Gauri\n*[[Keith Stevenson (actor)|Keith Stevenson]] as A. Tupper\n*[[Burbal (actor)|Birbal]] as Announcer\n*[[Sudhir (actor)|Sudhir]] as Kashyap\n*[[Paintal]]\n*[[Gufi Paintal]]\n*[[Sharat Saxena]]\n*[[Shekhar Wadhwan]]\n*[[Mridula Rani]]\n*[[Parvez Malik]]\n*[[Prem Sagar]]\n*[[Raj Mehra]]\n*[[Gurjinder Virk]]\n*[[Sayed Lane]]\n*[[Yusuf Khan (actor)|Yusuf Khan]]\n\n==Crew==\n*''Writer'' - [[Dev Anand]], [[Suraj Sanim]]\n*''Producer'' - [[Dev Anand]], [[Amit Khanna]]\n*''Production Company'' - [[Navketan International Films]], [[Navketan]]\n*''Cinematographer'' - [[Fali Mistry]], [[D. K. Prabhakar]]\n*''Music Director'' - [[Rajesh Roshan]]\n*''Lyricist'' - [[Amit Khanna]]\n*''Playback Singers'' - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Amit Kumar (singer)|Amit Kumar]], [[Manhar Udhas]], [[Vijay Benedict]],\n\n==Soundtrack==\nAll the songs<ref>http://www.hindigeetmala.net/movie/des_pardes.htm</ref> are composed by [[Rajesh Roshan]], with lyrics by [[Amit Khanna]].\n\n*Song \"Tu Pee Aur Jee\" was listed at #9 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n*Song \"Aap Kahen Aur Ham Na Aaye\" was listed at #13 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n* Song \"Jaisa Des Waisa Bhes\" was listed at #22 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n\n{| class=wikitable \n! #\n! Title\n! Singer(s)\n! Duration\n|-\n|1\n|\"Nazrana Bheja Kisine Pyar Ka\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]]\n|04:19\n|-\n|2\n|\"Ye Des Pardes\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]]\n|04:03\n|-\n|3\n|\"Aap Kahen Aur Ham Na Aaye\"\n|[[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n|05:38\n|-\n|4\n|\"Jaisa Des Waisa Bhes\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]], [[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n|04:47\n|-\n|5\n|\"Nazar Lage Naa Saathiyon\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]], [[Amit Kumar]], [[Vijay Benedict]], [[Manhar Udhas]]\n|04:29\n|-\n|6\n|\"Tu Pee Aur Jee\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]]\n|06:20\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0154390|Des Pardes}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120206014843/http://www.playlist.pk/ Des pardes music]\n\n[[Category:1978 films]]\n[[Category:1970s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dev Anand]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Rajesh Roshan]]\n", "text_old": "{{About||the 1983 film|Des Pardes (1983 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Des Pardes\n| image =Des Pardes (1978).jpg\n| caption =Poster\n| director = [[Dev Anand]]\n| producer = [[Dev Anand]]<br />Amit Khanna<br />Navketan<br />Navketan International Films\n| writer = [[Dev Anand]]<br />Suraj Sanim\n| narrator =\n| starring = [[Dev Anand]]<br />[[Tina Munim]]<br />[[Mehmood]]<br />[[Pran (actor)|Pran]]<br />[[Ajit Khan]]<br />[[Amjad Khan]]<br />[[Prem Chopra]]\n| music = [[Rajesh Roshan]]<br />[[Amit Khanna]] (lyrics)\n| cinematography = Fali Mistry<br />D. K. Prabhakar\n| editing =\n| distributor =\n| released = {{Film date|1978|6|29|df=y}}\n| runtime =\n| country = [[India]]\n| language = Hindi\n| budget =\n}}\n'''''Des Pardes''''' ({{lit|Home and Abroad}}) is a [[Bollywood films of 1978|1978]] Hindi film, produced and directed by [[Dev Anand]]. This family drama stars [[Dev Anand]] and [[Tina Munim]] (in her debut film), with [[Ajit Khan]], [[Pran (actor)|Pran]], [[Amjad Khan]], [[Shreeram Lagoo]], [[Tom Alter]], [[Bindu]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[A. K. Hangal]], [[Sujit Kumar]], [[Mehmood]] and [[Paintal]] in the supporting cast. For the first time, [[Dev Anand]] chose comparatively new music director [[Rajesh Roshan]] for this film, who did full justice to his selection as most of the songs became quite popular. The film received a Filmfare award for its sets and also received a nomination for best music director.\n\nThe message of this film is about the trend with some people, at the time, to earn money from foreign lands and that innocent ones being trapped and tormented by the illicit operators.\n\n== Plot ==\nSamir Sahni is a farmer living with his mom, dad, wife, Rama, a young daughter, and his younger brother, Veer. Samir gets an offer to work in the U.K., and departs accordingly. He would like to settle there, and after doing so, would like his family to also join him. The years go by, and Samir keeps in touch with his family regularly. Then the Sahni family stop receiving any letters from him, and are anxious to know what has happened to him. Veer is asked to travel to U.K. to find out, and he does so. What he finds are tens of thousands of East Indians on fake passports, working for less than minimum wages, poor unhealthy conditions, fear of being deported, and paying half of their earnings to fellow East Indians who had got them here through the underground. Veer finds no sign of his brother, and sets out to investigate, only to find deceit, murder, and that his very own life in danger.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Dev Anand]] as Veer Sahni\n*[[Pran (actor)|Pran]] as Samir Sahni\n*[[Gajanan Jagirdar]] as Mr. Sahni\n*[[Indrani Mukherjee]] as Rama Sahni\n*[[Ajit Khan]] as Gurnam\n*[[Tom Alter]] as Inspector Martin\n*[[Bindu (actress)|Bindu]] as Sylvia\n*[[Prem Chopra]] as Bansilal\n*[[A. K. Hangal]] as Pujari\n*[[Jankidas]] as Daiyal\n*[[Bharat Kapoor]] as Murarilal\n*[[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]] as Boota Singh / Avtar Singh\n*[[Sujit Kumar]] as Gangaram\n*[[Shreeram Lagoo]] as Mr. Burns\n*[[Mehmood Ali|Mehmood]] as Anwar\n*[[Tina Munim]] as Gauri\n*[[Keith Stevenson (actor)|Keith Stevenson]] as A. Tupper\n*[[Burbal (actor)|Birbal]] as Announcer\n*[[Sudhir (actor)|Sudhir]] as Kashyap\n*[[Paintal]]\n*[[Gufi Paintal]]\n*[[Sharat Saxena]]\n*[[Shekhar Wadhwan]]\n*[[Mridula Rani]]\n*[[Parvez Malik]]\n*[[Prem Sagar]]\n*[[Raj Mehra]]\n*[[Gurjinder Virk]]\n*[[Sayed Lane]]\n*[[Yusuf Khan (actor)|Yusuf Khan]]\n\n==Crew==\n*''Writer'' - [[Dev Anand]], [[Suraj Sanim]]\n*''Producer'' - [[Dev Anand]], [[Amit Khanna]]\n*''Production Company'' - [[Navketan International Films]], [[Navketan]]\n*''Cinematographer'' - [[Fali Mistry]], [[D. K. Prabhakar]]\n*''Music Director'' - [[Rajesh Roshan]]\n*''Lyricist'' - [[Amit Khanna]]\n*''Playback Singers'' - [[Kishore Kumar]], [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Amit Kumar (singer)|Amit Kumar]], [[Manhar Udhas]], [[Vijay Benedict]],\n\n==Soundtrack==\nAll the songs<ref>http://www.hindigeetmala.net/movie/des_pardes.htm</ref> are composed by [[Rajesh Roshan]], with lyrics by [[Amit Khanna]].\n\n*Song \"Tu Pee Aur Jee\" was listed at #9 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n*Song \"Aap Kahen Aur Ham Na Aaye\" was listed at #13 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n* Song \"Jaisa Des Waisa Bhes\" was listed at #22 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1978]]\n\n{| class=wikitable \n! #\n! Title\n! Singer(s)\n! Duration\n|-\n|1\n|\"Nazrana Bheja Kisine Pyar Ka\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]]\n|04:19\n|-\n|2\n|\